#week-title("Four", "Spiritual Discernment & Quarter III Preparation")

=== Core Teaching

One of the most significant risks in the mineral work — and in advanced inner
work — is the confusion of genuine signs of progress with wishful projection.
The tradition calls this "mistaking the sophist's colour for the philosopher's
colour": the practitioner who desperately wants to see the Peacock's Tail may
find iridescence in a film of oil on the glass's inner surface, or mistake the
natural colour of the starting material for a transformation that has not occurred.

*The discipline of discernment* is the capacity to distinguish:
- Genuine colour change in the preparation from the normal colour of its
  starting material
- The Peacock's Tail (iridescence arising from within the dissolved matter)
  from surface contamination or optical artefacts
- Genuine inner signs of progress (the Albedo's quality of spaciousness and
  lightening in the inner work) from mere emotional relief or temporary
  improvement in mood
- The Secret Fire operating in a preparation from the ordinary effects of
  gentle sustained heat on a complex chemical mixture

*How discernment is built.* The same way all alchemical perception is built:
through consistent observation, honest documentation, and comparison over time.
A practitioner who has been observing and photographing their preparation weekly
for six months has a perceptual memory of the preparation's evolution that
makes genuine changes unmistakeable. A practitioner who has maintained an
honest Desoille journal through genuine descents and genuine dawns has an inner
perceptual baseline against which actual progress is visible.

Discernment cannot be taught directly — it is built through the habit of honest
recording. The long-work log, the inner work journal, and the laboratory journal
together constitute the practitioner's instrument of discernment.

*Preparation for Quarter III Gathering.* The student assembles: all active
mineral preparations with current state documented; their full three-year
alchemical journal; the letter to a future Tyro (to be drafted this month).

=== Topics This Week

- Discernment: distinguishing genuine signs from wishful projection
